<subSubSection id="C36A65251468221023E3FE720B7E6A57" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCF36AE1468221023E3FE720B7E6A57" blockId="13.[151,1436,266,572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B904EABC1468221023E3FE720F1F69AF" bold="true" box="[198,319,426,452]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
Colleted off 
<collectingRegion id="49B4F84C1468221022F9FE720C0369AF" box="[476,547,426,452]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, from 
<quantity id="4C889B4B146822102154FE720D2F69AF" box="[625,783,426,452]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3299999999999996" metricValueMax="4.33" metricValueMin="2.33" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="333.0" valueMax="433.0" valueMin="233.0">233 to 433 m</quantity>
depth. All the characters of the 
<specimenCount id="9D76FD271468221027B0FE720B1469AF" box="[1173,1332,426,452]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" type="generic">12 specimens</specimenCount>
are very similar to those of the 
<typeStatus id="54CB880C146822102289FE0A0C326987" box="[428,530,466,492]" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D2D14682210211AFE0A0CEE6980" authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1887" box="[575,718,466,491]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Neobythites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ocellatus">
<emphasis id="B904EABC14682210211AFE0A0CEE6980" box="[575,718,466,491]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">N. ocellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nielsen 1999, Table 4). The anterior of the two dorsal fin ocelli is placed in front of a line through the anus and the posterior behind the line. 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D2D1468221027A1FE220B676A78" authorityName="Goode &amp; Bean" authorityYear="1885" box="[1156,1351,506,531]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Neobythites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="54" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gilli">
<emphasis id="B904EABC1468221027A1FE220B676A78" box="[1156,1351,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="54">Neobythites gilli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also characterized by having two distinct dorsal fin ocelli, but both are placed behind a line through the anus.
</paragraph>
